description.value: White glazed steatite scarab: engraved on the base with a symmetrical arrangement of a royal name, and other hieroglyphic signs, all within a rope border. In the centre the name of Antef V. On both sides the royal name is framed by a twig; on either side of the twigs are uraei on 'nb' signs. The goddess of Lower Egypt, Wadjet, is represented as a cobra; two snakes with the 'nb' sign signify "Ladies of Upper and Lower Egypt", i.e. Nekhbet and Wadjet. There is a hole pierced through longitudinally. Chipped and abraded.

legal.credit_line: © The Trustees of the British Museum
